On 27th Dec 2020, Vladimir Putin, President of the Russian Federation, and Tsenaev Dmitry Anatolyevych, Prime Minister of the Russian Federation, signed Government Resolution 2758 in December 2020, aimed at improving the business climate in the Russian real estate market. Under Article 10.1 of that resolution, real estate ownership (right to use) by a foreign legal entity or a foreign individual is set to a steady increase, and unrestricted ownership rights will start to apply to forex-non-residents only after 10 years. These measures provide the impetus to short and long term investors during 2021.

So, from today, many countries’ ‘Windows of Opportunity’ appear for Russia’ high-residential projects.
